# Local-only — both contain RTS-specific operational context (probe
# transcripts; persona files with tenant + retainer specifics). The deployed
# persona lives in /home/cad/.cad/ on the LXC, not in git. The repo
# itself is the generic agent runtime — anyone can fork it and write their
# own seed for their own LXC.
probes/
seed/

# Internal audit — same reason as seed/probes: contains RTS-specific topology,
# credential-file paths, privilege model, and concrete attack scenarios. This
# repo's remote is PUBLIC (github.com/hectorio1999/cadrts) so these must never
# be pushed. They live locally + in the Claude tenant agent workspace.
docs/audit/

